[![license](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-green.svg)](https://github.com/pilancilab/CLD)

## Model description

CLD attaches a small language-detection head to the (frozen) encoder of a pre-trained
ASR model and uses it to pick the language before decoding. Instead of a standard neural
network, the head is a **two-layer convex ReLU MLP** trained by solving a convex
reformulation with **CRONOS** — an ADMM solver (with preconditioned conjugate gradient /
Nyström preconditioning) implemented in **JAX**. This yields a **~13× training speedup**
over a standard NN head while matching or exceeding its accuracy, and is especially strong
in **low-resource** and **accent-diverse** regimes.

- **Backbone (frozen):** `{m['base']}`
- **Task:** spoken-language identification (5-way) → ASR language selection
- **Languages (5):**
{langs_list}
- **Class index → language:** {idx_map} (labels are the sorted ISO-639-1 codes)

## How it works

The head consumes **mean-pooled** encoder hidden states `X ∈ ℝ^(B×{m['dim']})`
(pooled over the time dimension) and computes, per class, `logits = relu(X @ W1) @ W2`,
then takes the `argmax`. The pickle stores a `CVX_ReLU_MLP` object whose key tensors are:

| Tensor | Shape | Role |
|---|---|---|
| `theta1` | `{m['theta1']}` | first-layer (ReLU) weights, per class |
| `theta2` | `(5, 128)` | output-layer weights, per class |

Configuration: `n_classes = 5`, `P_S = 64` hyperplane samples (→ 128 ReLU units),
input dim `{m['dim']}`.

## Intended uses & limitations

- **Use:** drop-in language detector for `{m['base']}` over the 5 languages above; pair
  with the **matching frozen base encoder** (embeddings are backbone-specific — a head is
  not transferable across backbones or to other languages).
- **Not** a standalone audio model: it is a head that runs on top of `{m['base']}`.
- Trained on Common Voice accents; strong but not unlimited generalization to unseen
  accents/domains. Extending the language set requires retraining.

## Training data

Pooled encoder embeddings derived from **Mozilla Common Voice** audio, accent-stratified
across the five languages (see the data recipe and `configs/` in the
[GitHub repo](https://github.com/pilancilab/CLD)). The convex head was fit on
~12,368 training / ~1,546 validation pooled embeddings extracted from the frozen
`{m['base']}` encoder.

## Training procedure

Trained with `train_cvxnn.py` (CRONOS / ADMM in JAX). Hyperparameters shared across all
three released backbones:

| rank | neurons | beta | rho | gamma_ratio | admm_iters | pcg_iters | opt_seed |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 20 | 64 | 0.001 | 0.1 | 1 | 6 | 32 | 1024 |

This model: `data_seed = {m['data_seed']}`, training time ≈ **{m['train_time']} s**,
estimated **{m['tflops']} TFLOPs**. (AdamW comparison config used elsewhere in the paper:
`gamma=1e-4, n_epoch=30, batch_size=1024`.)

